Tech Stack -> 
1. nextjs For Frontend
2. Node js Or Express
3. PostgreSQL(Relational)
4. Database (Graph) For Relation Ship 
5. Database (NoSQL/Posts) MongoDB 
6. Caching Layer Redis 
7. Asynchronous Messaging Apache Kafka
8. Frontend	Next.js	Fine
Backend	Node + Express	Fine
DB	PostgreSQL only	Add Mongo later if needed
Caching	Add Redis after something is slow	
Queues	Start with simple async jobs (BullMQ) before Kafka	
Graph DB	Only add if feed algorithm becomes complex (it won't at MVP stage)	


