## ‚úÖ Full System Architecture (Zero-cost but scalable)

| Component     | Tech                                             | Why                             | Cost              |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------- | ----------------- |
| Frontend      | Next.js (Vercel free)                            | Handles SSR + static pages      | ‚Çπ0                |
| Backend API   | Node.js (Railway / Render free)                  | Can scale to 10K users easily   | ‚Çπ0                |
| Main Database | PostgreSQL (Neon / Supabase / Railway free tier) | Proper relational DB            | ‚Çπ0                |
| Cache         | Self-hosted Redis on cheap VPS or KeyDB (free)   | For feed + sessions             | ‚Çπ0 if self-hosted |
| Message Queue | Kafka? No. Use **BullMQ + Redis** (free)         | Kafka is overkill for 10K users | ‚Çπ0                |
| Search        | Meilisearch / Typesense (self-hosted)            | Free + fast                     | ‚Çπ0                |
| File Storage  | Cloudflare R2 free / Supabase Storage free       | For images etc                  | ‚Çπ0                |
| Auth          | JWT / NextAuth (no auth0, no paid stuff)         | Free                            | ‚Çπ0                |
| Deployment    | Docker + Fly.io / Railway / Render free          | ‚Çπ0                              |                   |
| Monitoring    | Grafana + Prometheus (self-hosted)               | ‚Çπ0                              |                   |

So yes, 10K users can be handled **entirely free** if you know what you're doing.

