## ‚úÖ Step-by-Step Roadmap (No money, only skill)

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Define Requirements (Functional + Non-functional)

Don‚Äôt code without this. That‚Äôs how poor devs stay poor.

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ System Design (High-level architecture)

Draw before coding. CPU is cheaper than regret.

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Design Database Schema (PostgreSQL)

Entities:

* user
* tweet
* follow
* like
* retweet
* media
* notifications

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Write API Contracts (before writing backend)

Example:

```
POST /api/tweet
body: { text, media? }
response: { id, created_at }
```

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Set Up Dev Environment

* GitHub repo
* Prettier + ESLint
* .env file
* Docker file
* Dev DB local

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Build Core MVP Features

‚úÖ Signup / Login
‚úÖ Post tweet
‚úÖ Follow / Unfollow
‚úÖ Feed (fan-out or fan-in)
‚úÖ Like / Retweet

No DM, no search, no notifications, no video uploads until MVP works.

### 7Ô∏è‚É£ Add Caching (after proving DB bottleneck)

* Redis or KeyDB (self host on 1$ VPS or use free containers)

### 8Ô∏è‚É£ Add Background Jobs (BullMQ with Redis)

For:

* feed generation
* notifications
* email

### 9Ô∏è‚É£ Add Search (Meilisearch) ONLY if needed

### üîü Deploy Full Stack (all free services)

| Service  | Host                      |
| -------- | ------------------------- |
| Frontend | Vercel free               |
| Backend  | Railway / Render          |
| DB       | Neon / Supabase / Railway |
| Redis    | Fly.io self host          |
| Search   | Railway free container    |
| Storage  | Cloudflare R2             |

---

## ‚úÖ Scaling Strategy for 10K Users (Free Edition)

| Problem            | Solution                                           |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------------------------- |
| DB slow            | Add indexes + pagination                           |
| Feed slow          | Cache timelines in Redis                           |
| API slow           | Add rate limiting                                  |
| Server dying?      | Use horizontal scaling on free tier                |
| Storage limit?     | Move to Cloudflare R2 (free 10GB)                  |
| Free tier DB limit | Move DB to free PostgreSQL on Neon (up to 3M rows) |

---

## ‚ùå What NOT to use (because you're broke)

üõë Firebase (costs later)
üõë Paid Redis Cloud
üõë AWS / GCP (not for poor people)
üõë Kafka (overkill, eats RAM like a zombie)
üõë MongoDB for relational social graph

